articles.author: ABDULRAHMAN SHAHEEN, SARAH EL DEEB and ABBY SEWELL
articles.description: DAMASCUS, Syria (AP) — Ousted Syrian leader Bashar Assad fled to Moscow and received asylum from his longtime ally, Russian media said Sunday, hours after a stunning rebel advance seized control of Damascus and ended his family’s 50 years of iron rule.
articles.title: Ousted Syrian leader Assad flees to Moscow after fall of Damascus, Russian state media say

articles.author: JON GAMBRELL
articles.description: MANAMA, Bahrain (AP) — For Iran’s theocratic government, it keeps getting worse. Its decadeslong strategy of building an “Axis of Resistance” supporting militant groups and proxies around the region is falling apart.
articles.title: Analysis: Collapse of Syria's Assad is a blow to Iran's 'Axis of Resistance'

articles.author: KAREEM CHEHAYEB
articles.description: BEIRUT (AP) — Abu Mohammed al-Golani, the militant leader whose stunning insurgency toppled Syria’s President Bashar Assad, has spent years working to remake his public image, renouncing longtime ties to al-Qaida and depicting himself as a champion of pluralism and tolerance.
articles.title: Who is Abu Mohammed al-Golani, the leader of the insurgency that toppled Syria's Assad?

articles.author: BILL BARROW and WILL WEISSERT
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Donald Trump said he can't guarantee that his promised tariffs on key U.S.
articles.title: Trump says he can't guarantee tariffs won't raise US prices and won't rule out revenge prosecutions

articles.author: MICHAEL R. SISAK and CEDAR ATTANASIO
articles.description: NEW YORK (AP) — Police don't know who he is, where he is, or why he did it. As the frustrating search for UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson’s killer got underway for a fifth day Sunday, investigators reckoned with a tantalizing contradiction: They have troves of evidence, but the shooter remains an enigma.
articles.title: The hunt for UnitedHealthcare CEO's elusive killer yields new evidence, but few answers

articles.author: ELLEN KNICKMEYER and JOANNA KOZLOWSKA
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Donald Trump on Sunday pushed Russian leader Vladimir Putin to act to reach an immediate ceasefire with Ukraine, describing it as part of his active efforts as president-elect to end the war despite being weeks from taking office.
articles.title: Trump calls for immediate ceasefire in Ukraine and says a US withdrawal from NATO is possible

articles.author: WAFAA SHURAFA and SAMY MAGDY
articles.description: DEIR AL BALAH, Gaza Strip (AP) — Israeli airstrikes in central Gaza killed at least 14 people including children Sunday, Palestinian health officials said, while the bombing of a hospital in northern Gaza wounded a half-dozen patients.
articles.title: Gaza health officials say latest Israeli airstrikes kill at least 14 including children

articles.author: LAURIE KELLMAN and KIM TONG-HYUNG
articles.description: SEOUL, South Korea (AP) — In an era of rising authoritarianism, at the heels of a six-hour martial law decree that unfolded while many South Koreans slept, something noteworthy happened: Democracy held.
articles.title: South Korea's democracy held after a 6-hour power play. What does it say for democracies elsewhere?

articles.author: TIA GOLDENBERG
articles.description: TEL AVIV, Israel (AP) — Shortly after Donald Trump’s win in last month’s U.S. election, Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu rushed to congratulate the president-elect: “History’s greatest comeback!” he gushed.
articles.title: Trump's return may be a boon for Netanyahu, but challenges abound in a changed Middle East

articles.author: EDDIE PELLS
articles.description: The new, 12-team College Football Playoff brings with it a promise to be bigger, more exciting, more lucrative.
articles.title: First 12-team College Football Playoff set, Oregon seeded No. 1 and SMU edges Alabama for last spot
